Content:: Vicente Cavalcante Fialho (27 January 1938 – 12 July 2022) was a Brazilian engineer and politician. A member of the Liberal Front Party, he served as mayor of Fortaleza from 1971 to 1975[1] and served in the Chamber of Deputies from 1991 to 1995.[2] Fialho died of COVID-19 in Fortaleza on 12 July 2022, at the age of 84.[3] This article about a Brazilian politician is a stub.
